OL,7,F"That picture changed my life," he
OL,8,Fsays. "I just wanted to help people on
OL,9,Fthat day and I can just remember
OL,10,Fhearing the shutters of the cameras
OL,11,Fgoing click, click, click."
OL,13,F"I was now being held up as this
OL,14,Fheroic poster boy, but people had died
OL,15,Funderground. I found it very difficult
OL,16,Fto deal with."
OL,18,FEx-fireman Paul Dadge told ITV he felt
OL,19,F"vulnerable" when he became a "heroic
OL,20,Fposter boy" of the 7/7 London bombings
